cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning locomotion for a quadrupedal robot. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses Deep Reinforcement Learning and Evolutionary Strategies to learn the locomotion behavior. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an architecture for learning complex behaviors. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses controlling the behavior of a robot. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely category as the paper only uses 4-dimensional IMU observations, but it is still possible as the paper may use computer vision techniques in future work.
